2
00:00:28,370 --> 00:00:30,480

3
00:00:32,840 --> 00:00:38,820

4
00:00:49,363 --> 00:00:50,863

5
00:01:42,110 --> 00:01:43,605
This was done by a beast.

6
00:01:43,605 --> 00:01:47,652
A tiger came into Hanseong and murdered twelve people.

7
00:01:47,652 --> 00:01:50,751
I'm sure it was the same tiger.

8
00:01:53,601 --> 00:01:56,124
Three people have already died.

9
00:01:56,124 --> 00:01:58,521
Why isn't anyone coming?

10
00:01:59,202 --> 00:02:02,358
Are the Hanseong Ministry and Police Bureau not doing anything about this?

11
00:02:07,067 --> 00:02:08,908
- Go after it. 
 - Your Highness.

12
00:02:08,908 --> 00:02:11,994
Your Highness! Let's go!

13
00:02:17,721 --> 00:02:21,174
Woo Ik, go east and stop the tiger from going down to the private homes.

14
00:02:21,175 --> 00:02:22,690
Yes, Your Highness.

15
00:02:26,768 --> 00:02:28,320
Let's go!

16
00:02:52,944 --> 00:02:54,549
Your Highness.

17
00:02:57,894 --> 00:02:59,465
He's still alive.

18
00:02:59,465 --> 00:03:01,521
It must have known it was being chased.

19
00:03:01,521 --> 00:03:04,979
It left behind the food it was dragging.

20
00:03:05,602 --> 00:03:07,237
That tiger knows about people.

21
00:03:07,237 --> 00:03:10,033
It's very cunning and smart.

22
00:03:10,545 --> 00:03:12,822
You save him and take him to the Village Hospital.

23
00:03:12,822 --> 00:03:14,213
Yes.

24
00:03:31,419 --> 00:03:33,686
We rejoice at your safe return!

25
00:03:33,687 --> 00:03:35,625
How could you leave the palace without the King's permission?

26
00:03:35,626 --> 00:03:39,317
Do you know how worried I was?

27
00:04:18,565 --> 00:04:22,289
What happened to the man who was taken to the Village Hospital?

28
00:04:23,327 --> 00:04:27,779
He was treated by the doctor but couldn't be saved.

29
00:04:30,073 --> 00:04:34,285
Starting today, take all the private bodyguards and chase that tiger.

30
00:04:34,285 --> 00:04:37,333
Your Highness, we need His Majesty's permission.

31
00:04:37,333 --> 00:04:40,710
I will write an appeal to His Majesty.

32
00:04:40,710 --> 00:04:43,336
We must get his permission—

33
00:04:47,127 --> 00:04:51,979
Your Highness!

34
00:04:53,354 --> 00:04:55,668
You dare to try to assassinate the Crown Prince?

35
00:04:55,668 --> 00:04:58,602
No... that is not true! I'm just an apprentice maid!

36
00:04:58,602 --> 00:05:00,983
Hurry and save His Highness first.

37
00:05:00,983 --> 00:05:03,041
You go in first.

38
00:05:03,896 --> 00:05:06,596
I'm afraid of water.

39
00:05:06,596 --> 00:05:08,516
You're scaring me!

40
00:05:08,517 --> 00:05:10,495
Do not worry!

41
00:05:10,495 --> 00:05:12,833
I will bring him back!

42
00:05:14,821 --> 00:05:16,021
- Your Highness! 
 - Hurry and untie this for me!

43
00:05:16,022 --> 00:05:19,624
Take his hands! Your Highness!

44
00:05:19,624 --> 00:05:21,983
Be careful, Your Highness! She might be an assassin!

45
00:05:21,984 --> 00:05:24,893
No, I'm not! I'm just an apprentice maid!

46
00:05:24,893 --> 00:05:27,840
Are you all right, Your Highness?

47
00:05:27,840 --> 00:05:29,532
 She could be an assassin, Your Highness!

48
00:05:29,533 --> 00:05:32,343
I will protect you, Your Highness!

49
00:05:32,344 --> 00:05:33,724
Are you all right?

50
00:05:33,725 --> 00:05:35,086
Why can I not take off my armor?

51
00:05:35,089 --> 00:05:39,137
I will help you. Don't worry!

52
00:05:39,137 --> 00:05:41,378
Are you all right, Your Highness?

53
00:05:41,379 --> 00:05:43,544
Let me help you up…

54
00:05:43,544 --> 00:05:46,549
- Your Highness! 
 - Your Highness!

55
00:05:48,230 --> 00:05:51,054
Your Highness! Your Highness!

56
00:05:51,054 --> 00:05:52,726
- Your Highness. 
 - Your Highness.

57
00:05:52,726 --> 00:05:54,806
Are you all right?

58
00:05:54,806 --> 00:05:56,344
Your Highness.

59
00:06:02,328 --> 00:06:04,342
Your Highness.

60
00:06:04,342 --> 00:06:07,950
Your Highness. Your Highness.

61
00:06:07,950 --> 00:06:09,774
You!

62
00:06:12,600 --> 00:06:14,962
Your Highness.

63
00:06:14,962 --> 00:06:17,887
I have committed a grave sin.

64
00:06:19,145 --> 00:06:21,926
If you forgive me this once,

65
00:06:21,926 --> 00:06:27,103
I will be deeply indebted and never forget your generosity.

66
00:06:27,103 --> 00:06:32,812
Please forgive this foolish and inadequate girl, Your Highness.

67
00:06:32,812 --> 00:06:35,607
His Highness has already left.

68
00:06:37,377 --> 00:06:38,916
Pardon?

69
00:06:39,874 --> 00:06:44,741
He wants you to write a letter of apology.

70
00:06:44,741 --> 00:06:47,507
A letter of apology?

71
00:06:47,507 --> 00:06:49,709
Is that all I need to do?

72
00:06:49,709 --> 00:06:53,004
Try your best.

73
00:06:53,004 --> 00:06:57,124
Bring it to the Crown Prince's quarters in three days.

74
00:07:07,205 --> 00:07:10,128
Will a letter of apology suffice?

75
00:07:19,900 --> 00:07:22,055
I still can't believe it!

76
00:07:22,055 --> 00:07:26,378
I can't believe I'm transcribing a book with His Majesty's granddaughters.

77
00:07:26,378 --> 00:07:31,019
We can share refreshments like companions.

78
00:07:31,019 --> 00:07:34,826
Deok Im is running late.

79
00:07:35,651 --> 00:07:39,696
What if the princesses arrive first?

80
00:07:40,885 --> 00:07:43,430
She's the first one to do it.

81
00:07:45,516 --> 00:07:47,216
Deok Im!

82
00:07:51,386 --> 00:07:52,975
Deok Im!

83
00:07:58,177 --> 00:08:02,521
- How on earth...? 
 - Why are you soaking wet?

84
00:08:05,983 --> 00:08:09,006
Deok Im, what happened?

85
00:08:14,605 --> 00:08:18,161
Wow! So you met our older brother?

86
00:08:18,161 --> 00:08:20,260
Yes, Your Highness.

87
00:08:20,260 --> 00:08:22,386
How did he look?

88
00:08:22,386 --> 00:08:26,895
Don't you think he's handsome?

89
00:08:26,895 --> 00:08:30,469
I shouldn't dare to look straight at His Highness's face so...

90
00:08:30,469 --> 00:08:35,423
True. Did he not say anything else?

91
00:08:38,656 --> 00:08:40,013
Actually,

92
00:08:40,013 --> 00:08:44,301
I received punishment for doing something wrong.

93
00:08:44,301 --> 00:08:49,247
It's not a huge punishment. He wants me to write a letter of apology.

94
00:08:49,247 --> 00:08:51,218
A letter of apology?

95
00:08:56,246 --> 00:09:00,904
Deok Im! If it's too much for you, you can come to my house.

96
00:09:00,904 --> 00:09:03,125
All right?

97
00:09:03,125 --> 00:09:05,649
You can come to mine as well.

98
00:09:05,649 --> 00:09:07,166
Excuse me?

99
00:09:09,527 --> 00:09:13,527
If it were me, I wouldn't have let Young Hee and Bok Yeon join you.

100
00:09:13,527 --> 00:09:17,986
Yes, we are close, but it is true that they have bad handwriting.

101
00:09:17,986 --> 00:09:19,723
Just because they asked, you accepted.

102
00:09:19,723 --> 00:09:22,057
You have to work all night to fix their mistakes.

103
00:09:22,057 --> 00:09:24,079
We have nothing to gain.

104
00:09:24,079 --> 00:09:26,194
Why are you so foolish?

105
00:09:26,194 --> 00:09:30,469
What do you mean by "we didn't gain anything"? We saw their happy faces.

106
00:09:30,469 --> 00:09:34,147
It's not even a big deal. It only allowed us to work together.

107
00:09:34,150 --> 00:09:36,428
And they are already that happy about it.

108
00:09:36,428 --> 00:09:38,948
So is this how you're going to live?

109
00:09:38,948 --> 00:09:42,562
Kyung Hee, we are all palace maids, after all.

110
00:09:42,562 --> 00:09:45,060
We can never leave the Palace.

111
00:09:45,060 --> 00:09:47,951
Whether we gain or lose...

112
00:09:47,951 --> 00:09:50,672
What's the point?

113
00:09:52,172 --> 00:09:56,239
There is not much I can do here as who I truly am.

114
00:09:56,239 --> 00:09:58,654
Even if it's trivial, it's okay.

115
00:09:58,654 --> 00:10:01,617
I want to live my life by making choices.

116
00:10:02,276 --> 00:10:05,420
I decided to let Young Hee and Bok Yeon join.

117
00:10:05,420 --> 00:10:07,475
It was my decision.

118
00:11:03,607 --> 00:11:05,263
Let's light up and be wary of everything.

119
00:11:05,264 --> 00:11:06,904
 Yes, Sir!

120
00:11:26,235 --> 00:11:29,020
Make sure the King doesn't find out.

121
00:11:29,020 --> 00:11:30,553
Yes, Sir!

122
00:11:38,266 --> 00:11:40,000
His Highness is waiting.

123
00:11:40,000 --> 00:11:41,456
Yes.

124
00:11:44,100 --> 00:11:48,772

125
00:12:18,336 --> 00:12:19,847
I will convene a meeting.

126
00:12:19,847 --> 00:12:23,425
Your Highness, let's wait for daybreak.

127
00:12:24,285 --> 00:12:27,452
If you move now, the King will find out.

128
00:12:27,452 --> 00:12:29,670
If His Majesty were to find out about the contents of this anonymous letter...

129
00:12:29,670 --> 00:12:33,137
I don't know if it will be beneficial or harmful.

130
00:12:33,137 --> 00:12:35,758
Are you certain, Your Highness?

131
00:12:40,993 --> 00:12:43,827
I will catch the criminal for you.

132
00:12:43,827 --> 00:12:47,825
Even if it takes several years or even decades,

133
00:12:47,825 --> 00:12:50,261
I will definitely catch him.

134
00:12:52,121 --> 00:12:54,766
Will you wait for me?

135
00:12:56,997 --> 00:13:01,294
Several decades is too much.

136
00:13:06,750 --> 00:13:10,050

137
00:13:14,211 --> 00:13:15,989
"I have made a grave mistake."

138
00:13:15,990 --> 00:13:19,811
"Your Highness's generosity of forgiving me."

139
00:13:19,811 --> 00:13:23,828
"It will be deeply engraved in my bones."

140
00:13:23,828 --> 00:13:28,434
"I will definitely pay you back."

141
00:13:28,434 --> 00:13:33,722
"May you live a long life. Long live the King!"'

142
00:13:34,883 --> 00:13:38,383
It's finished. It's perfect!

143
00:13:38,383 --> 00:13:40,025
Deok Im!

144
00:13:40,723 --> 00:13:42,723
Do this for me.

145
00:13:45,529 --> 00:13:48,884
Sa Wol isn't good at this.

146
00:13:51,383 --> 00:13:53,394
My Lady.

147
00:13:53,394 --> 00:13:59,362
When does His Highness normally feel best?

148
00:14:00,258 --> 00:14:02,513
I'm not sure.

149
00:14:02,513 --> 00:14:04,788
Usually during his snack time,

150
00:14:04,788 --> 00:14:08,481
or when he's chatting with the local government officials.

151
00:14:09,553 --> 00:14:11,408
Why do you ask?

152
00:14:12,483 --> 00:14:16,150
Just curious.

153
00:14:16,150 --> 00:14:19,942
Why are you curious?

154
00:14:19,942 --> 00:14:22,133
Actually…

155
00:14:23,273 --> 00:14:25,940
My Lady, the Head Court Lady is here.

156
00:14:25,940 --> 00:14:30,517
- Help me up… 
 - Hurry, My Lady!

157
00:14:39,940 --> 00:14:43,073
There is no special news in the  jobo . 
  (T/N: Jobo - State Newspaper)

158
00:14:43,073 --> 00:14:48,263
I heard His Majesty and the Queen, Her Highness, are resting comfortably.

159
00:14:48,730 --> 00:14:50,297
But…

160
00:14:50,297 --> 00:14:54,208
I think something happened in the Crown Prince Palace last night.

161
00:14:54,208 --> 00:14:57,180
The light was on all night.

162
00:14:57,739 --> 00:14:59,983
I hope it's nothing.

163
00:14:59,983 --> 00:15:02,447
I'm worried for some reason.

164
00:15:03,466 --> 00:15:07,733
When the Crown Prince's palace maids come back from their duty, report back to me.

165
00:15:07,733 --> 00:15:09,816
Yes, My Lady.

166
00:15:09,816 --> 00:15:12,516
I hope you have a great day.

167
00:15:12,516 --> 00:15:15,292
Yes, My Lady.

168
00:15:22,189 --> 00:15:28,245
I have a feeling His Highness won't be in a good mood.

169
00:15:29,765 --> 00:15:32,854
I don't feel like working this morning.

170
00:16:09,491 --> 00:16:12,735
Good morning, Kitty!

171
00:17:02,400 --> 00:17:07,690

172
00:17:10,180 --> 00:17:11,890

173
00:17:13,590 --> 00:17:15,590

174
00:17:17,660 --> 00:17:19,970

175
00:17:22,540 --> 00:17:26,090

176
00:17:37,019 --> 00:17:40,241

(T/N: Daehak Yeonibo - Supplement to the Exposition on the Great Learning written by Qiu Jun, a Confucian scholar, and politician; It's about how to become a great leader)

177
00:17:41,472 --> 00:17:44,228

178
00:17:44,228 --> 00:17:47,695

179
00:17:47,695 --> 00:17:49,795
 In ruling a country…

180
00:17:49,796 --> 00:17:54,422
 Nothing is more urgent than providing for the people.

181
00:17:54,422 --> 00:17:56,861
 This particular phrase in the Supplement to the Exposition on the Great Learning...

182
00:17:56,861 --> 00:18:01,218
 I think it is a virtue that you have to keep in mind forever, Your Highness.

183
00:18:01,218 --> 00:18:03,408
 I will bear that in mind.

184
00:18:03,408 --> 00:18:06,564
 Your Highness, instead of the king of a country,

185
00:18:06,564 --> 00:18:10,172
 have you ever wanted to be just an ordinary man?

186
00:18:10,172 --> 00:18:11,818
 Not even once.

187
00:18:11,818 --> 00:18:16,529
 Have you ever felt that being a crown prince was a burden?

188
00:18:16,530 --> 00:18:20,387
 How can a person who received Heaven's will complain?

189
00:18:20,387 --> 00:18:24,874
As the Crown Prince, I can read as much as I want.

190
00:18:24,874 --> 00:18:27,883
I have well-informed people around me.

191
00:18:27,883 --> 00:18:32,434
It is worthwhile to use my good fortune entirely for the sake of Joseon.

192
00:18:32,434 --> 00:18:34,510
I can't trade it for anything.

193
00:18:34,510 --> 00:18:37,523
 But is it not still difficult?

194
00:18:37,523 --> 00:18:41,897
How can I complain when there are people that are starving?

195
00:18:41,897 --> 00:18:43,477
I wear silk clothes, and

196
00:18:43,478 --> 00:18:47,799
I eat great food. If I still complain,

197
00:18:47,799 --> 00:18:50,257
I would be a worthless person.

198
00:18:50,257 --> 00:18:53,456
That is an excellent answer, Your Highness.

199
00:18:53,456 --> 00:18:56,456
The heavenly commandments come down to me.

200
00:18:56,456 --> 00:19:01,470
In the future, I will carry the fate of the entire nation.

201
00:19:02,137 --> 00:19:04,215
I won't hide or run away

202
00:19:04,215 --> 00:19:09,113
from the heavenly commandments.

203
00:19:27,698 --> 00:19:31,677
All the court ladies are afraid of His Highness.

204
00:19:31,677 --> 00:19:34,307
They call him "The Tiger Crown Prince."

205
00:19:34,885 --> 00:19:39,707
Where the Crown Prince is located is called the Goblin's Square.

206
00:19:39,707 --> 00:19:43,597
But I think the Crown Prince

207
00:19:44,290 --> 00:19:46,623
is an admirable person.

208
00:20:18,700 --> 00:20:20,870

209
00:20:52,465 --> 00:20:53,976
Are you the maid in charge of looking after this library?

210
00:20:53,976 --> 00:20:55,487
Yes.

211
00:20:59,138 --> 00:21:02,160
You can see the class location well from here.

212
00:21:03,588 --> 00:21:07,010
You can hear everything, right?

213
00:21:12,520 --> 00:21:15,576
Did you see or hear anything suspicious recently?

214
00:21:15,577 --> 00:21:17,418
Pardon?

215
00:21:17,418 --> 00:21:19,997
Don't make me ask you twice.

216
00:21:19,997 --> 00:21:23,340
Was there anyone who snooped around here secretly?

217
00:21:24,590 --> 00:21:27,413
Did you not see any spies?

218
00:21:27,413 --> 00:21:30,586
Who in the world is spying on who?

219
00:21:30,586 --> 00:21:33,242
Who are you, by the way?

220
00:21:33,243 --> 00:21:38,131
Who are you to suddenly come in and ask me these questions?

221
00:21:38,131 --> 00:21:39,831
I am…

222
00:21:42,920 --> 00:21:45,109
You don't need to know.

223
00:22:01,815 --> 00:22:06,015
Now you feel like talking.

224
00:22:07,349 --> 00:22:09,959
Are you trying to bribe a palace maid with this little money?

225
00:22:09,960 --> 00:22:11,748
Is five  nyang  not enough? 
  (T/N: nyang - old Korean currency)

226
00:22:11,749 --> 00:22:14,863
Do you think I'm only worth five  nyang ?

227
00:22:17,884 --> 00:22:20,259
This is the Crown Prince's library.

228
00:22:20,259 --> 00:22:23,015
Even if he doesn't come here because it's old and shabby,

229
00:22:23,015 --> 00:22:25,422
it still belongs to the Crown Prince His Highness for sure.

230
00:22:25,422 --> 00:22:29,318
Also, even though I'm still an apprentice maid, I'm the Crown Prince's palace maid.

231
00:22:29,318 --> 00:22:33,115
How dare you bribe His Highness's subject?

232
00:22:37,017 --> 00:22:40,861
Are you… His Highness's subject?

233
00:22:40,862 --> 00:22:43,728
I said I'm the Crown Prince's maid, didn't I?

234
00:22:48,565 --> 00:22:51,532
As if a mere maid has the quality of loyalty.

235
00:22:52,389 --> 00:22:54,778
Please leave at once.

236
00:22:58,789 --> 00:23:01,666
What do you think you're doing?

237
00:23:05,753 --> 00:23:07,343
Stop it.

238
00:23:07,343 --> 00:23:08,964
This is dirty!

239
00:23:08,964 --> 00:23:10,843
I know it is dirty. Stop it!

240
00:23:10,843 --> 00:23:13,189
- Get out of here. Get out! 
 - Didn't I tell you to stop?

241
00:23:13,190 --> 00:23:15,756
- I will… I will leave on my own.
 - Out! Out!

242
00:23:15,757 --> 00:23:18,248
How dare you touch me!

243
00:23:18,248 --> 00:23:22,348
I told you to wait!

244
00:23:22,348 --> 00:23:25,328
How dare you!

245
00:23:25,328 --> 00:23:27,941
Do you know who I am?

246
00:23:27,941 --> 00:23:29,598
I am…

247
00:23:29,598 --> 00:23:31,287
I…

248
00:23:37,686 --> 00:23:40,786
I'm the master here.

249
00:23:40,786 --> 00:23:44,519
He's strange for a normal-looking person.

250
00:24:04,331 --> 00:24:06,242
What are you doing?

251
00:24:07,021 --> 00:24:10,044
I definitely gave it back.

252
00:24:10,044 --> 00:24:13,565
Money that fell on the floor has no owner, so someone has to take it.

253
00:24:13,565 --> 00:24:15,100
What are you talking about?

254
00:24:15,101 --> 00:24:18,224
Stop your nonsense and go to the Head Court Lady.

255
00:24:18,225 --> 00:24:20,120
She's asking for you.

256
00:24:21,876 --> 00:24:24,020
In the middle of the night?

257
00:24:36,127 --> 00:24:38,249
I'm sorry for calling you this late.

258
00:24:38,249 --> 00:24:41,686
I would like to assign you a new transcribing job.

259
00:24:42,687 --> 00:24:45,553
- It's Jujadaejon. 
 - Pardon? 
  (T/N: Jujadaejon is a book of Anthologies in the Joseon dynasty)

260
00:24:46,799 --> 00:24:48,544
Can you do it?

261
00:24:48,544 --> 00:24:51,110
I'm sorry.

262
00:24:51,110 --> 00:24:54,281
I'm still working on The Supplement to the Exposition on the Great Learning. It's out of my limit.

263
00:24:54,282 --> 00:24:56,701
You're doing well though.

264
00:24:56,701 --> 00:25:00,962
Well... I wasn't the only one working on it...

