00:25:00,962 --> 00:25:06,030
Even with others' help, it is still your work.

266
00:25:07,960 --> 00:25:09,060

267
00:25:19,136 --> 00:25:21,203
I am sorry.

268
00:25:24,454 --> 00:25:26,310
I knew it.

269
00:25:27,798 --> 00:25:30,165
I like you.

270
00:25:35,230 --> 00:25:38,510

271
00:25:45,933 --> 00:25:49,189
All the money in the country comes from the people.

272
00:25:49,189 --> 00:25:52,834
If you don't limit yourself and a deficit comes in the area you need to use,

273
00:25:52,834 --> 00:25:56,573
it affects the people.

274
00:25:56,573 --> 00:26:00,088
I'll finish with the Supplement to the Exposition on the Great Learning.

275
00:26:00,088 --> 00:26:01,670
Please take a rest.

276
00:26:01,670 --> 00:26:04,424
I will be back in 30 minutes.

277
00:26:16,590 --> 00:26:18,280

(The Supplement to the Exposition on the Great Learning)

278
00:26:55,788 --> 00:26:57,776

(The Supplement to the Exposition on the Great Learning)

279
00:27:04,288 --> 00:27:06,276
You know what?

280
00:27:06,276 --> 00:27:10,155
I'm scared of you.

281
00:27:11,335 --> 00:27:15,124
Are you scared because it's too precious for an apprentice maid to have?

282
00:27:15,124 --> 00:27:19,123
You scared me. You didn't make any noise.

283
00:27:19,799 --> 00:27:24,610
I wonder how you managed to get something so precious.

284
00:27:27,681 --> 00:27:31,848
Please go back. No matter how much you ask, it's no use.

285
00:27:34,048 --> 00:27:38,981
You said you won't accept money and whatnot. You were so arrogant.

286
00:27:40,839 --> 00:27:42,861
I was foolish.

287
00:27:42,861 --> 00:27:45,621
It was right in front of me, yet I didn't suspect it.

288
00:27:45,621 --> 00:27:48,321
What are you talking about?

289
00:27:49,482 --> 00:27:53,662
You call yourself the Crown Prince's maid and the Crown Prince's subject?

290
00:27:53,663 --> 00:27:55,698
Let me go!

291
00:27:55,698 --> 00:27:58,953
Who are you? Give me your name.

292
00:27:58,953 --> 00:28:02,022
Why would I tell my name to a lowly apprentice maid?

293
00:28:02,022 --> 00:28:04,362
Don't look down on an apprentice maid.

294
00:28:04,362 --> 00:28:07,362
One day I'll become a level-five Court Lady.

295
00:28:07,363 --> 00:28:11,393
- Really? 
  - A level-five Court Lady.

296
00:28:11,393 --> 00:28:16,021
 One day I'll become a level-five Court Lady.

297
00:28:17,193 --> 00:28:19,605
That girl was also an apprentice maid.

298
00:28:36,025 --> 00:28:38,491
- Explain yourself. 
 - Excuse me?

299
00:28:38,491 --> 00:28:40,692
Why were you eavesdropping on the Crown Prince's class session?

300
00:28:40,692 --> 00:28:43,503
And why did you have the book the Crown Prince was learning about?

301
00:28:43,503 --> 00:28:45,768
Explain yourself!

302
00:28:47,470 --> 00:28:49,162
Transcribing job?

303
00:28:49,162 --> 00:28:52,159
A lot of the palace maids do it on their days off as their secondary job.

304
00:28:52,159 --> 00:28:53,416
The Daehak Yeonibo, though? 
  (The Supplement to the Exposition on the Great Learning)

305
00:28:53,417 --> 00:28:55,880
I didn't want to do it because it was too hard.

306
00:28:55,880 --> 00:28:59,333
It's not like I can choose.

307
00:29:03,530 --> 00:29:05,641
Did you really work on this?

308
00:29:05,641 --> 00:29:08,395
- Pardon? 
 - You are not a court lady with a lot of experience.

309
00:29:08,395 --> 00:29:09,730
How can a mere apprentice maid

310
00:29:09,730 --> 00:29:12,540
like you have such great handwriting?

311
00:29:22,710 --> 00:29:24,980

312
00:29:34,310 --> 00:29:35,720

313
00:29:43,530 --> 00:29:46,830

314
00:29:46,830 --> 00:29:48,643
There's no way.

315
00:29:49,350 --> 00:29:50,953
How can a mere apprentice maid…

316
00:29:50,953 --> 00:29:54,521
You keep saying "mere apprentice maid" and look down on me.

317
00:29:54,521 --> 00:29:57,209
What makes you so special?

318
00:29:57,209 --> 00:30:00,557
Does being a  Siganggwan  make you special? 
 (T/N: Siganggwan - a level-four official in the Crown Prince Academy)

319
00:30:00,557 --> 00:30:01,737
What do you mean?

320
00:30:01,737 --> 00:30:04,980
I knew you sounded familiar.

321
00:30:04,980 --> 00:30:08,430
Over there. You're one of the lecturers that assist the Crown Prince.

322
00:30:08,430 --> 00:30:09,960
Aren't I right?

323
00:30:13,940 --> 00:30:15,380
Yes,

324
00:30:15,380 --> 00:30:16,608
I am the Crown Prince's lecturer.

325
00:30:16,608 --> 00:30:18,784
What's your name?

326
00:30:21,380 --> 00:30:23,519
It's Hong Deok Ro.

327
00:30:24,270 --> 00:30:25,720
 Sir Preceptor,

328
00:30:25,720 --> 00:30:27,980
that's what I am.

329
00:30:27,980 --> 00:30:29,966
Sir Preceptor?

330
00:30:31,140 --> 00:30:33,074
Liar.

331
00:30:33,074 --> 00:30:35,363
What?

332
00:30:35,363 --> 00:30:37,800
I am the Royal Preceptor.

333
00:30:37,800 --> 00:30:41,359
I heard he was really handsome.

334
00:30:41,359 --> 00:30:47,010
- What? 
 - Since he's the most handsome in Hanseong, I heard he's very sought after.

335
00:30:47,650 --> 00:30:50,230
You're disappointed

336
00:30:50,230 --> 00:30:51,480
now that you have seen me?

337
00:30:51,487 --> 00:30:55,576
You know how rumors are.

338
00:30:57,740 --> 00:30:59,970
The words and actions of the Crown Prince

339
00:30:59,970 --> 00:31:02,320
should not be overheard.

340
00:31:02,320 --> 00:31:06,440
I will let you go today since I don't have proof.

341
00:31:07,460 --> 00:31:09,070
You...

342
00:31:09,070 --> 00:31:11,950
better be careful.

343
00:31:25,620 --> 00:31:28,955
The "most handsome in Hanseong."

344
00:31:39,270 --> 00:31:40,550
Hey.

345
00:31:40,550 --> 00:31:43,020
Did you just throw salt on me?

346
00:31:47,910 --> 00:31:50,605
Open this door when I'm still kind.

347
00:31:50,605 --> 00:31:52,497
Hurry!

348
00:31:52,497 --> 00:31:53,650
What

349
00:31:53,650 --> 00:31:55,590
do you think you're…

350
00:32:07,970 --> 00:32:09,693
Salt?

351
00:32:12,120 --> 00:32:13,805
How…

352
00:32:24,070 --> 00:32:26,153
How…

353
00:32:28,510 --> 00:32:30,025
Your Highness.

354
00:32:35,340 --> 00:32:37,790
The "most handsome man"

355
00:32:37,790 --> 00:32:39,374
"in Hanseong."

356
00:32:39,374 --> 00:32:42,207
- Excuse me? 
 - It's nothing.

357
00:32:45,050 --> 00:32:46,500
Your Highness.

358
00:32:49,290 --> 00:32:50,510
I'm sorry

359
00:32:50,510 --> 00:32:52,130
but see me for a second.

360
00:33:16,070 --> 00:33:18,674
It's a report posted by the Police Bureau.

361
00:33:18,674 --> 00:33:19,973
Please read it.

362
00:33:19,973 --> 00:33:21,784
 (Gyebon: documents submitted when asking the king about a big issue)

363
00:33:23,550 --> 00:33:24,846
That's okay.

364
00:33:24,846 --> 00:33:27,490
What's the use of reading excuses from incompetent people?

365
00:33:27,490 --> 00:33:29,901
You seem very irritated.

366
00:33:30,570 --> 00:33:33,482
The Crown Prince's palace maids

367
00:33:33,482 --> 00:33:35,805
complain to me that you scare them.

368
00:33:36,800 --> 00:33:39,801
Who cares what they say?

369
00:33:39,801 --> 00:33:41,660
If it involved me,

370
00:33:41,660 --> 00:33:43,920
would you listen?

371
00:33:44,610 --> 00:33:47,130
I feel kind of heavy

372
00:33:47,130 --> 00:33:49,320
knowing my master's mind is not at ease.

373
00:33:51,500 --> 00:33:54,192
I want to take you somewhere.

374
00:35:02,150 --> 00:35:04,963
Is today the palace maids' festival day?

375
00:35:04,963 --> 00:35:06,520
It's in ten days.

376
00:35:06,520 --> 00:35:07,810
They are just rehearsing.

377
00:35:07,810 --> 00:35:09,770
If they are all playing like that,

378
00:35:09,770 --> 00:35:11,499
who is taking care of their superiors?

379
00:35:11,499 --> 00:35:14,563
The other court ladies are taking care of it.

380
00:35:15,540 --> 00:35:17,410
They seem excited.

381
00:35:17,410 --> 00:35:21,410
The Eunuch Officer and the guards are also coming to see them on the festival day.

382
00:35:22,450 --> 00:35:24,900
Seeing the palace maids having fun...

383
00:35:24,900 --> 00:35:26,000
Does that make you upset?

384
00:35:26,000 --> 00:35:28,898
They're useless games.

385
00:35:30,690 --> 00:35:34,600
Never mind. They got royal assent afterall.

386
00:35:34,600 --> 00:35:38,925
 Line up! Sung Deok Im is about to read a book!

387
00:35:38,925 --> 00:35:42,478
 Please line up!

388
00:35:42,478 --> 00:35:46,047
This storyteller doesn't come every day.

389
00:35:46,048 --> 00:35:50,330
Line up! Sung Deok Im is reading!

390
00:35:50,330 --> 00:35:54,561
Line up! Sung Deok Im is reading!

391
00:35:54,561 --> 00:35:58,529
Come on, this storyteller does not come every day.

392
00:35:58,529 --> 00:36:02,164
 Line up! Sung Deok Im is reading!

393
00:36:02,164 --> 00:36:05,234
Please line up!

394
00:36:05,234 --> 00:36:10,323
 Line up! Sung Deok Im is reading!

395
00:36:26,400 --> 00:36:28,661
The novel I'm reading today…

396
00:36:28,661 --> 00:36:31,183
It's set in the royal family of the Han Dynasty.

397
00:36:31,183 --> 00:36:35,050
It's a story of two brothers' tragedy.

398
00:36:44,110 --> 00:36:48,830
"We are brothers born from the same womb"

399
00:36:48,830 --> 00:36:53,360
"Why does the King hate only me?"

400
00:36:54,100 --> 00:36:56,390
"As you grow up,"

401
00:36:56,390 --> 00:36:59,270
"my worries grow bigger."

402
00:37:00,020 --> 00:37:01,740
"Because of you,"

403
00:37:01,740 --> 00:37:03,577
"I'm no longer"

404
00:37:03,577 --> 00:37:05,687
"needed."

405
00:37:06,910 --> 00:37:08,950
"The more he likes you,"

406
00:37:08,950 --> 00:37:11,550
"the more he hates me."

407
00:37:11,550 --> 00:37:13,690
"Hate ripens as"

408
00:37:13,690 --> 00:37:15,960
"the kindness deepens."

409
00:37:16,630 --> 00:37:18,466
"Young brother…"

410
00:37:18,466 --> 00:37:19,860
"you"

411
00:37:19,860 --> 00:37:22,580
"were born to kill me."

412
00:37:23,540 --> 00:37:26,287
"Because of you, I lost my father's favor."

413
00:37:26,287 --> 00:37:30,230
"I'm... forever in despair."

414
00:37:30,230 --> 00:37:31,920
"Because you and I are brothers,"

415
00:37:31,920 --> 00:37:34,470
"we always look alike."

416
00:37:34,470 --> 00:37:36,140
"How did"

417
00:37:36,140 --> 00:37:38,460
"our situation change so much?"

418
00:37:43,850 --> 00:37:45,231
 I told you not to come.

419
00:37:45,231 --> 00:37:47,249
 But…

420
00:37:48,130 --> 00:37:51,395
 I heard you were leaving the Palace.

421
00:37:52,350 --> 00:37:56,109
 I wanted to give a proper goodbye to Father His Highness.

422
00:37:56,109 --> 00:37:57,820
 He just wanted

423
00:37:57,820 --> 00:38:00,850
 to say farewell to his parents.

424
00:38:00,850 --> 00:38:02,741
 Do you not know your own son?

425
00:38:02,741 --> 00:38:06,194
 I don't even know my parents. Would I know my son?

426
00:38:06,910 --> 00:38:08,627
 Go away!

427
00:38:09,420 --> 00:38:13,016
 His Majesty says he's only taking you with him!

428
00:38:25,640 --> 00:38:27,880
 Grandfather

429
00:38:27,880 --> 00:38:30,790
 is only taking me.

430
00:38:30,790 --> 00:38:33,679
 Then what about Father…

431
00:38:33,679 --> 00:38:36,853
 I'm not needed as long as that child exists.

432
00:38:40,760 --> 00:38:43,601
 He was born to kill me!

433
00:38:43,601 --> 00:38:47,935
 - No! 
 - He was born to kill me!

434
00:38:53,490 --> 00:38:55,980
 No!

435
00:38:57,720 --> 00:39:01,073
 "You were born to kill me."

436
00:39:01,073 --> 00:39:04,540
 He was born to kill me.

437
00:39:05,320 --> 00:39:08,447
 That's all for today!

438
00:39:11,760 --> 00:39:14,967
 Please read more!

439
00:39:17,590 --> 00:39:19,410
Let's go back.

440
00:39:19,410 --> 00:39:20,836
Yes.

441
00:39:24,800 --> 00:39:30,770

442
00:39:48,100 --> 00:39:50,908
Are you still transcribing at night?

443
00:39:53,470 --> 00:39:56,130
Is all that money

444
00:39:56,130 --> 00:39:58,160
not enough?

445
00:39:58,160 --> 00:39:59,270
What…

446
00:39:59,270 --> 00:40:01,380
Why are you here?

447
00:40:01,380 --> 00:40:04,430
I just needed a place to be alone.

448
00:40:04,430 --> 00:40:06,198
You are the intruder.

449
00:40:06,198 --> 00:40:09,600
All right. Then stay alone.

450
00:40:13,000 --> 00:40:15,620
Are you making enough money?

451
00:40:15,620 --> 00:40:16,708
Pardon?

452
00:40:16,708 --> 00:40:18,030
I'm talking about the  paegwansoseol .

453
00:40:18,030 --> 00:40:19,780
 (T/N: Paegwansoseol - a folktale novel)

454
00:40:20,470 --> 00:40:21,950
People

455
00:40:21,950 --> 00:40:23,380
like it.

456
00:40:23,380 --> 00:40:25,355
I don't.

457
00:40:25,355 --> 00:40:27,930
Novels only mess up my mind.

458
00:40:28,610 --> 00:40:31,583
It stimulates false curiosity.

459
00:40:31,583 --> 00:40:34,927
It just makes people curious about the end.

460
00:40:43,100 --> 00:40:45,442
You just

461
00:40:45,442 --> 00:40:49,024
make money by using your tricks.

462
00:40:50,190 --> 00:40:53,148
No matter how the listener feels

463
00:40:53,148 --> 00:40:55,127
doesn't matter to you.

464
00:40:56,090 --> 00:40:59,228
How did you know I read books?

465
00:40:59,228 --> 00:41:01,518
Did you come to the palace maids' residence?

466
00:41:01,518 --> 00:41:03,744
You could get in real trouble.

467
00:41:03,745 --> 00:41:06,110
Don't read.

468
00:41:06,110 --> 00:41:09,210
You're not supposed to read books to people.

469
00:41:28,610 --> 00:41:31,707
How dare he?

470
00:41:31,707 --> 00:41:34,774
He told me to stop reading books.

471
00:41:34,774 --> 00:41:36,853
What do you think?

472
00:41:36,853 --> 00:41:41,007
- Deok Im. 
 - In the first place, it was him that eavesdropped on me reading a book!

473
00:41:54,000 --> 00:41:56,390
Here is more work.

474
00:41:56,390 --> 00:41:58,301
Can you do it alone?

475
00:41:58,301 --> 00:42:00,112
Yes, My Lady.

476
00:42:00,112 --> 00:42:02,420
Let me know if you can't handle it.

477
00:42:02,420 --> 00:42:05,220
If you don't say it first,

478
00:42:05,220 --> 00:42:08,270
no one will know.

479
00:42:08,270 --> 00:42:10,405
Don't worry.

480
00:42:25,460 --> 00:42:26,762
Deok Im,

481
00:42:26,762 --> 00:42:30,151
if you really met the Sir Preceptor,

482
00:42:30,151 --> 00:42:33,755
don't curse him in front of others.

483
00:42:33,755 --> 00:42:36,506
- Why not? 
 - You might get arrested.

484
00:42:36,506 --> 00:42:40,396
You might be dragged into a well in the middle of the night.

485
00:42:40,396 --> 00:42:42,180
By whom?

486
00:42:45,230 --> 00:42:47,449
You have to pick it once.

487
00:42:56,870 --> 00:42:59,207
 What is this?

488
00:42:59,207 --> 00:43:01,794
 - Why do we have to do this every day?
- Let's not this anymore.

489
00:43:04,060 --> 00:43:05,460
I got it.

490
00:43:05,460 --> 00:43:08,540
I got it.

491
00:43:08,540 --> 00:43:11,721
You will get it tomorrow.

492
00:43:11,721 --> 00:43:14,144
Deok Im, Young Hee!

493
00:43:14,144 --> 00:43:16,770
I got it!

494
00:43:16,770 --> 00:43:20,092
I'll bring water to Sir Preceptor tomorrow morning.

495
00:43:20,092 --> 00:43:22,280
Water? What water?

496
00:43:22,280 --> 00:43:23,900
Every time Sir Preceptor

497
00:43:23,900 --> 00:43:25,810
comes to the Palace, every morning,

498
00:43:25,810 --> 00:43:28,398
he drinks water by the well.

499
00:43:28,398 --> 00:43:31,580
I will give it to him tomorrow morning.

500
00:43:31,580 --> 00:43:34,376
I'm so happy!

501
00:43:46,260 --> 00:43:49,387
 Sir Preceptor is so wonderful!

502
00:43:49,387 --> 00:43:53,255
 When he passes by

503
00:43:54,760 --> 00:43:56,508
 I can feel a spring breeze.

504
00:43:56,508 --> 00:43:58,350
Spring breeze, my foot.

505
00:43:58,350 --> 00:44:00,840
It's more like a gust whenever he opens his mouth.

506
00:44:01,640 --> 00:44:05,575
There are a lot of women who are infatuated with someone like that.

507
00:44:05,575 --> 00:44:07,750
I don't understand.

508
00:44:20,280 --> 00:44:23,092
Are you all right?

509
00:44:25,680 --> 00:44:27,821
I am fine.

510
00:44:27,821 --> 00:44:30,811
If one side doesn't move, you can't go through it.

511
00:44:30,811 --> 00:44:32,390
I will get out of the way

512
00:44:32,390 --> 00:44:34,290
so go ahead.

513
00:44:47,150 --> 00:44:48,725
Miss Young Maiden!

514
00:45:01,670 --> 00:45:03,876
You dropped this.

515
00:45:09,880 --> 00:45:12,163
It suits you.

516
00:45:23,630 --> 00:45:26,763
If that was Sir Preceptor,

517
00:45:28,260 --> 00:45:30,135
I would understand why.

518
00:45:39,180 --> 00:45:41,160
Your Majesty,

519
00:45:41,160 --> 00:45:43,206
Sir Preceptor is here.

520
00:45:43,206 --> 00:45:46,349
 Let him come in.

521
00:45:59,530 --> 00:46:00,990
Your Majesty.

522
00:46:00,990 --> 00:46:02,690
Did you call me?

523
00:46:02,690 --> 00:46:06,227
Come here and sit.

524
00:46:14,170 --> 00:46:16,680
Hey, Deok Ro!

525
00:46:16,680 --> 00:46:19,030
About the Crown Prince.

526
00:46:19,030 --> 00:46:23,053
He appeals every single day.

527
00:46:23,053 --> 00:46:25,550
He's going to kill me

528
00:46:25,550 --> 00:46:28,350
before he catches the tiger.

529
00:46:28,350 --> 00:46:30,020
And

530
00:46:30,020 --> 00:46:33,980
he shouldn't use his private bodyguards to catch a tiger.

531
00:46:33,980 --> 00:46:38,730
His bodyguards are there to protect the Crown Prince.

532
00:46:38,730 --> 00:46:42,205
Where does he want to send them?

533
00:46:42,205 --> 00:46:45,770
I'll go to the Crown Prince Palace and deliver Your Majesty's royal command.

534
00:46:45,770 --> 00:46:48,354
Go ahead.

535
00:46:48,354 --> 00:46:49,820
Your Majesty!

536
00:46:49,820 --> 00:46:52,800
There is something you need to ask.

537
00:46:53,420 --> 00:46:56,713
Three days ago, the lights in Crown Prince Palace were on all night.

538
00:46:56,713 --> 00:47:00,069
Yes, I forgot.

539
00:47:00,080 --> 00:47:02,260
All right.

540
00:47:02,260 --> 00:47:04,560
Did something happen?

541
00:47:05,560 --> 00:47:07,389
Do you not know?

542
00:47:07,389 --> 00:47:09,368
He doesn't seem to know.

543
00:47:09,369 --> 00:47:12,725
If he doesn't know, then who does?

544
00:47:12,725 --> 00:47:18,750
Or the Crown Prince should come in person and explain it to Your Majesty.

545
00:47:18,750 --> 00:47:21,222
I think I know the answer.

546
00:47:21,222 --> 00:47:23,386
Really?

547
00:47:24,660 --> 00:47:27,903
Soon, there will be the palace maids' festival.

548
00:47:27,903 --> 00:47:30,702
It is something that I permitted.

549
00:47:31,560 --> 00:47:33,710
It is a game night for the palace maids.

550
00:47:33,710 --> 00:47:36,280
There are many people watching secretly.

551
00:47:36,280 --> 00:47:38,720
I guess His Highness

552
00:47:38,720 --> 00:47:41,490
watched it all night long.

553
00:47:42,570 --> 00:47:46,386
I watched the night sky late into the night.

554
00:47:47,170 --> 00:47:51,830
You should have watched it with me.

555
00:47:51,830 --> 00:47:55,162
On that day, I will set up a place in my quarters.

556
00:47:55,162 --> 00:47:56,973
I will have you over there.

557
00:47:56,973 --> 00:47:59,708
Of course.

558
00:48:05,960 --> 00:48:07,500
 His Highness

559
00:48:07,500 --> 00:48:10,760
 asked you to write a letter of apology.

560
00:48:13,170 --> 00:48:15,590
Are you here to see His Highness?

561
00:48:15,590 --> 00:48:16,494
Yes.

562
00:48:16,494 --> 00:48:19,074
His Highness is at Jonhyeongak Hall.
  (T/N: Jonhyeongak/Jonhyeon Hall: a building where the Crown Prince's educational activities took place)

563
00:48:19,074 --> 00:48:22,207
You can go straight this way.

564
00:48:22,207 --> 00:48:24,260
Thank you.

565
00:48:27,520 --> 00:48:31,644
He just went to Kyungwondang quarters.

566
00:48:40,080 --> 00:48:42,216
He's in Cheonhanjeong Royal Portrait Hall.

567
00:49:10,746 --> 00:49:12,713
Yes.

568
00:49:12,713 --> 00:49:17,124
Have you ever lived in a pine valley with a stream?

569
00:49:17,124 --> 00:49:19,352
Wol Hye!

570
00:49:19,352 --> 00:49:22,250
It is you, Deok Im!

571
00:49:28,899 --> 00:49:30,966
Why do you make a fuss about that?

572
00:49:30,966 --> 00:49:33,565
Of course, he would tease a young apprentice maid.

573
00:49:33,565 --> 00:49:39,371
After you officially become a palace maid, there will be a terrible hazing ritual.

574
00:49:39,371 --> 00:49:40,942
A hazing ritual?

575
00:49:40,942 --> 00:49:45,309
Everyone goes through it so you don't have to be scared in advance.

576
00:49:45,309 --> 00:49:48,320
Why are you here today?

577
00:49:53,601 --> 00:49:58,290
Great. You're only an apprentice maid, and you already made a bad impression.

578
00:50:00,776 --> 00:50:06,387
Your Highness, Apprentice Maid Sung Deok Im would like to see you.

579
00:50:08,681 --> 00:50:11,826
He said to come in.

580
00:50:29,105 --> 00:50:31,117
I am Sung Deok Im.

581
00:50:31,117 --> 00:50:36,200
I am here to give you the apology letter you asked for.

582
00:51:03,076 --> 00:51:07,720
He orders you to bring that letter.

583
00:51:12,244 --> 00:51:15,905
"The generosity of the Crown Prince His Highness"

584
00:51:15,905 --> 00:51:19,055
"for forgiving me"—

585
00:51:19,055 --> 00:51:22,182
Who told you to read it? Bring it here.

586
00:51:22,183 --> 00:51:23,776
Excuse me?

587
00:51:34,290 --> 00:51:35,970

588
00:51:37,350 --> 00:51:39,290
 This handwriting…

589
00:51:41,410 --> 00:51:44,320

590
00:51:44,320 --> 00:51:46,520
 No way.

591
00:51:49,276 --> 00:51:52,520
 What? Was it you?

592
00:52:31,170 --> 00:52:33,692
The first line is wrong.

593
00:52:35,740 --> 00:52:38,151
The next one too.

594
00:52:38,151 --> 00:52:40,700
And the next one.

595
00:52:46,805 --> 00:52:48,883
It is disrespectful!

596
00:52:48,883 --> 00:52:51,690
I'm sorry, Your Highness.

597
00:53:11,676 --> 00:53:16,610
His Highness orders you to correct the mistakes and rewrite one.

598
00:53:25,702 --> 00:53:29,050
I don't know when he will come.

599
00:53:31,092 --> 00:53:35,170
Maybe I should be honest to Lady Seo.

600
00:53:50,637 --> 00:53:54,370
It is the well water that you always drink, Sir.

601
00:54:00,544 --> 00:54:02,990
Just let me know what you need.

602
00:54:02,990 --> 00:54:04,960
What do you need?

603
00:54:06,630 --> 00:54:09,586
I cannot waste my time.

604
00:54:09,586 --> 00:54:11,760
If you have something to say, say it already.

605
00:54:19,187 --> 00:54:22,610
I don't know what the mistakes are.

606
00:54:31,934 --> 00:54:35,360
I'm not sure why you don't know.

607
00:54:38,199 --> 00:54:41,370
Please teach me, Sir.

608
00:54:45,710 --> 00:54:47,287
Tiger.

609
00:54:47,287 --> 00:54:49,054
Excuse me?

610
00:54:49,054 --> 00:54:53,537
Find all the books about tigers in this library.

611
00:54:53,537 --> 00:54:55,768
Tigers?

612
00:54:55,768 --> 00:54:59,907
It would take a long time to find all of them.

613
00:54:59,907 --> 00:55:03,650
Of course, I will find everything for you.

614
00:55:07,250 --> 00:55:12,694
"The generosity of the Crown Prince His Highness for forgiving me—

615
00:55:12,694 --> 00:55:14,429
Wait.

616
00:55:15,419 --> 00:55:17,574
When did he ever forgive you?

617
00:55:17,574 --> 00:55:19,152
Sorry?

618
00:55:19,973 --> 00:55:22,084
The reason for the letter of apology

619
00:55:22,084 --> 00:55:26,563
is to decide whether to forgive or not based on the content.

620
00:55:26,563 --> 00:55:31,314
The reason why you fell into the pond

621
00:55:31,314 --> 00:55:35,992
why you were running around like a goby in the solemn Palace,

622
00:55:35,992 --> 00:55:38,684
those are the things you should write down in detail.

623
00:55:43,899 --> 00:55:47,933
Especially this part... Do you not value your life?

624
00:55:47,933 --> 00:55:53,785
Eternity is only for His Majesty. How dare you say it to His Highness?

625
00:55:53,785 --> 00:55:55,374
I didn't know…

626
00:55:55,374 --> 00:56:00,208
I'm sure you wrote everything that sounds good.

627
00:56:00,799 --> 00:56:05,431
Thank you. I know what to fix now.

628
00:56:05,431 --> 00:56:10,567
Next time, I'm sure my apology letter will get a pass.

629
00:56:47,780 --> 00:56:49,980

630
00:57:04,450 --> 00:57:06,800

631
00:57:24,460 --> 00:57:26,020

632
00:57:37,060 --> 00:57:39,050

633
00:57:44,645 --> 00:57:46,578
Your Highness.

634
00:57:54,460 --> 00:57:56,110

635
00:58:08,815 --> 00:58:10,960
How dare you!

636
00:58:14,010 --> 00:58:16,500

637
00:58:26,650 --> 00:58:28,272
I…

638
00:58:33,350 --> 00:58:34,930

639
00:58:42,560 --> 00:58:43,750

640
00:58:47,520 --> 00:58:48,640

641
00:58:51,490 --> 00:58:53,200

642
00:59:01,677 --> 00:59:03,522
A hundred times.

643
00:59:11,013 --> 00:59:15,113
His Highness asks that you rewrite

644
00:59:15,113 --> 00:59:18,324
the wrong words each a hundred times.

645
00:59:44,027 --> 00:59:46,600
I told you to wait and see.

646
00:59:47,130 --> 00:59:49,574
A pay cut would be better.

647
00:59:49,574 --> 00:59:51,693
I would prefer a whipping.

648
00:59:51,693 --> 00:59:54,594
I'm sick and tired of apology letters.

649
00:59:54,594 --> 00:59:56,713
What is wrong with a letter of apology?

650
00:59:56,713 --> 00:59:59,613
You are given a chance to realize your mistakes.

651
00:59:59,613 --> 01:00:03,436
A chance, my foot. Even a worm will turn.

652
01:00:03,436 --> 01:00:07,927
Every time I think of His Highness, sleep seems to elude me.

653
01:00:07,927 --> 01:00:11,920
How will he become a good king if he irritates his inferiors like this?

654
01:00:15,114 --> 01:00:17,803
Do you dare to insult the Crown Prince?

655
01:00:17,803 --> 01:00:20,047
Just take this.

656
01:00:29,383 --> 01:00:31,638
So, this map was here all along.

657
01:00:31,638 --> 01:00:32,848
Do you recognize that?

658
01:00:32,848 --> 01:00:35,658
My father had this.

659
01:00:36,867 --> 01:00:41,367
Never mind. I needed this map. I'm glad you found it.

660
01:00:48,138 --> 01:00:50,150
What kind of map is it?

661
01:00:50,150 --> 01:00:51,464
It's  Doseonjeongdo . 
  (T/N: Doseongjeondo - The map of the capital)

662
01:00:51,464 --> 01:00:53,455
That's nothing special though.

663
01:00:53,455 --> 01:00:55,920
The area where mountain animals are often found.

664
01:00:55,920 --> 01:00:58,599
 Chakho Gapsa 's hunting routes. 
  (T/N: Chakho Gapsa - Military specially selected for tigers)

665
01:00:58,599 --> 01:01:04,101
The places of nets and  chalco  are all marked. 
  (T/N: Chalco is a tool used to catch animals)

666
01:01:04,101 --> 01:01:07,638
It'll help us to catch that tiger.

667
01:01:07,638 --> 01:01:10,990
I was wondering why you were investigating tigers.

668
01:01:10,990 --> 01:01:14,060
Is it because of the tiger in the city?

669
01:01:14,060 --> 01:01:16,580
Another person died yesterday.

670
01:01:17,319 --> 01:01:20,990
If the map helps, I will look for more.

671
01:01:31,256 --> 01:01:34,545
The training records of the tiger hunting soldiers will help, too, right?

672
01:01:58,013 --> 01:02:00,602
Should I thank you…?

673
01:02:10,077 --> 01:02:15,114
What I going to say is really important, so listen carefully, Lady Seo.

674
01:02:15,114 --> 01:02:16,792
Yes?

675
01:02:18,606 --> 01:02:22,683
The apprentice maid that comes to Crown Prince Palace with an apology letter, you know.

676
01:02:22,683 --> 01:02:25,349
You said she's your pupil, Lady Seo.

677
01:02:27,733 --> 01:02:29,410
Yes.

678
01:02:30,170 --> 01:02:35,042
Every time she appears, His Highness's cold symptoms seem to get worse.

679
01:02:35,042 --> 01:02:38,708
His sore throat gets worse and he would stutter.

680
01:02:38,708 --> 01:02:40,953
He seems to be losing all his senses.

681
01:02:40,953 --> 01:02:42,142
No way!

682
01:02:42,143 --> 01:02:46,686
Have you heard of the flu ghost?

683
01:02:46,686 --> 01:02:50,062
Is there such a ghost?

684
01:02:50,062 --> 01:02:53,561
I think that flu ghost is attached to that apprentice maid.

685
01:02:53,561 --> 01:02:58,198
Now that ghost seems to have attached itself to His Highness.

686
01:02:58,198 --> 01:03:00,245
Then…

687
01:03:00,245 --> 01:03:03,356
Should I go to the Ritual Hall and request an exorcism?

688
01:03:03,356 --> 01:03:05,990
That's a good idea.

689
01:03:08,450 --> 01:03:10,720
Wait.

690
01:03:17,604 --> 01:03:19,204
A flu ghost?

691
01:03:19,205 --> 01:03:22,849
Do you believe in such a myth?

692
01:03:22,849 --> 01:03:25,165
What do mean by the Ritual Hall?

693
01:03:25,165 --> 01:03:27,809
It's been a while since we banned exorcism among our court subjects.

694
01:03:27,809 --> 01:03:30,580
But…

695
01:03:41,956 --> 01:03:45,034
You can leave now.

696
01:03:45,034 --> 01:03:47,470
Yes, Your Highness.

697
01:03:58,538 --> 01:04:01,127
- Come sit near me. 
 - I'm sorry, Your Highness.

698
01:04:01,127 --> 01:04:05,061
I was the one who mentioned that flu ghost, but...

699
01:04:05,061 --> 01:04:07,810
Don't make me say it twice.

700
01:04:20,086 --> 01:04:24,018
Isn't this the map used by the tiger hunting soldiers?

701
01:04:24,018 --> 01:04:26,362
It will be a big help.

702
01:04:26,362 --> 01:04:30,150
First, I should check this route with my bodyguards.

703
01:04:30,150 --> 01:04:34,055
Your Highness, what about His Majesty's permission?

704
01:04:34,055 --> 01:04:36,266
I couldn't get it.

705
01:04:37,127 --> 01:04:39,982
Will that be okay?

706
01:04:39,982 --> 01:04:44,430
Twenty-seven have already died. I can't wait any longer.

707
01:04:44,980 --> 01:04:47,409
Tell them to gather up by  Haeshi.
(T/N: Haeshi: 9-11 pm)

708
01:04:47,409 --> 01:04:49,540
Yes, Your Highness.

709
01:04:49,540 --> 01:04:54,132
"How could I not repent?"

710
01:04:54,132 --> 01:04:57,988
"You can cut my salary or whip me."

711
01:04:57,988 --> 01:05:05,452
"The reason why you asked me to write a letter of apology is that you wanted to give me a chance to reflect on my own mistake."

712
01:05:05,452 --> 01:05:10,560
"I'm deeply grateful for your kindness."

713
01:05:27,130 --> 01:05:29,130

714
01:05:29,130 --> 01:05:30,870

715
01:05:30,870 --> 01:05:33,730
 Isn't she something?

716
01:06:28,694 --> 01:06:32,227
Write a new letter of apology.

717
01:06:32,227 --> 01:06:34,661
The topic is…

718
01:06:34,661 --> 01:06:40,307
The crime of thinking about something else on the inside while pretending not to.

719
01:06:40,307 --> 01:06:44,560
The crime of writing a fancy letter.

720
01:07:09,211 --> 01:07:11,840
She's gone insane.

721
01:07:17,149 --> 01:07:19,860
Do you have another question?

722
01:07:19,860 --> 01:07:22,117
No.

723
01:07:22,117 --> 01:07:25,663
You're having a hard time catching a tiger that kills people.

724
01:07:25,663 --> 01:07:28,388
It's not even your job.

725
01:07:28,388 --> 01:07:30,477
Who else would do it?

726
01:07:30,477 --> 01:07:31,590
Well...

727
01:07:31,590 --> 01:07:34,147
Hanseong Ministry pawn off its responsibility on the Police Bureau.

728
01:07:34,147 --> 01:07:38,608
The Police Bureau is stuck on the tiger-hunting soldiers, which don't exist anymore.

729
01:07:39,418 --> 01:07:44,050
People die every day, but no one is responsible.

730
01:07:44,610 --> 01:07:47,096
So I have no choice but to step up.

731
01:07:49,013 --> 01:07:51,324
That's very admirable!

732
01:07:53,818 --> 01:07:57,918
I mean it. You're admirable.

733
01:08:01,000 --> 01:08:05,500
W- Why are you laughing?

734
01:08:07,499 --> 01:08:09,650
Now that I think about it…

735
01:08:10,170 --> 01:08:13,534
I've only seen you in the library.

736
01:08:13,534 --> 01:08:16,113
What do you usually do?

737
01:08:16,113 --> 01:08:18,612
The same.

738
01:08:18,612 --> 01:08:23,695
Transcribing books or reading them to people.

739
01:08:23,695 --> 01:08:26,975
I don't like sewing so I don't do it often.

740
01:08:26,975 --> 01:08:31,252
Are you still reading folktale novels to people?

741
01:08:32,500 --> 01:08:35,622
I told you not to read them.

742
01:08:35,622 --> 01:08:39,125
Why do you care whether I read a book or not?

743
01:08:39,125 --> 01:08:40,391
This is my order!

744
01:08:40,391 --> 01:08:44,228
So why should I follow that order?

745
01:08:44,228 --> 01:08:47,225
Are you my superior?

746
01:08:51,696 --> 01:08:54,640
I'm going to read a book tonight after all.

747
01:08:54,640 --> 01:08:55,656
What?

748
01:08:55,656 --> 01:08:58,668
Today is the festival day of the palace maids.

749
01:08:58,668 --> 01:09:03,050
I'm going to gather all the maids and read a book for them.

750
01:09:10,377 --> 01:09:14,100
What? Do you want me to fill in tonight?

751
01:09:14,100 --> 01:09:15,556
I'm sorry.

752
01:09:15,556 --> 01:09:16,768
By myself?

753
01:09:16,771 --> 01:09:19,404
Everyone else will be at the festival, but I'm the only one on duty?

754
01:09:19,404 --> 01:09:22,919
What can I do? This is from His Highness.

755
01:09:22,919 --> 01:09:26,020
Why? Are you going to dispute this to him?

756
01:09:43,863 --> 01:09:45,852
Gae! 
  (T/N: Gae: moving a token 2 steps forward on the gameboard)

757
01:09:59,563 --> 01:10:01,218
Your Highness.

758
01:10:01,751 --> 01:10:04,384
- Based on the size of the toenail... 
 - Your Highness.

759
01:10:16,529 --> 01:10:20,384
The traces of the tiger continue to the Palace.

760
01:10:20,384 --> 01:10:22,143
Let's go back to the palace right now.

761
01:10:22,143 --> 01:10:23,930
Yes, Sir!

762
01:10:47,100 --> 01:10:51,520

763
01:11:18,090 --> 01:11:19,614
Follow me!

764
01:11:19,614 --> 01:11:22,670
What's going on?

765
01:11:28,318 --> 01:11:30,096
Why are you doing this?

766
01:11:30,096 --> 01:11:32,495
I'll explain on the way.

767
01:11:33,330 --> 01:11:35,719
Give me a reason first.

768
01:11:36,561 --> 01:11:38,694
I know it will be dangerous.

769
01:11:38,694 --> 01:11:43,132
But you're the only one. You're the only one who can do this.

770
01:11:43,132 --> 01:11:45,032
Excuse me?

771
01:11:45,032 --> 01:11:46,192
What on earth—

772
01:11:46,192 --> 01:11:48,013
Read a book.

773
01:11:53,536 --> 01:11:55,420
I ask of you.

774
01:11:56,125 --> 01:12:00,290
Read a book in front of people.

775
01:12:14,820 --> 01:12:20,720

776
01:12:22,260 --> 01:12:24,670

777
01:12:24,670 --> 01:12:31,560
♫  If it's something you've been waiting for all the time  ♫

778
01:12:31,560 --> 01:12:33,320
♫  Nothing to hesitate  ♫

779
01:12:33,320 --> 01:12:36,400

~ Preview ~

780
01:12:36,400 --> 01:12:37,269
 A tiger?

781
01:12:37,269 --> 01:12:38,956
 Do you have a plan?

782
01:12:38,957 --> 01:12:42,493
 There's always the right time for everything.

783
01:12:42,493 --> 01:12:44,808
 Let's wait and see.

784
01:12:44,808 --> 01:12:47,573
 Do we have to wait until all the palace maids become tiger food?

785
01:12:47,573 --> 01:12:49,500
 I think that's the answer.

786
01:12:49,500 --> 01:12:53,388
 Please save us!

787
01:12:53,388 --> 01:12:55,671
 Deok Im, can we do this?

788
01:12:55,671 --> 01:12:59,415
 You guys help me. I'm going to make sure no one gets hurt and gets out of here.

789
01:12:59,415 --> 01:13:03,750
 I'm going to read a book.

790
01:13:03,750 --> 01:13:07,350
♫  I will be here  ♫
